,Recommended,280040,15676617,"Posted: 3 May, 2015",all,goblin girl,"A Wizard's Lizard is a pleasant, vaguely Zelda-like procedurally generated action game. You play the familiar of a wizard who has been abducted by Death, and you must find your way through a series of dungeons to face down the monster and rescue him.Naturally, this isn't something you're going to be able to do on a single life. For most of your attempts at the game you're going to be gathering money, paying to upgrade the village store, rescuing villagers who will then assist you the next time you play, and learning how best to handle the various traps, monsters, and bosses you face. Expect to die, die, die, die, DIE, each time starting your next game with a few more options than last time.Additional note: If you wanted to play The Binding of Isaac but that game's blood-soaked graphics and child abuse theme turned you off, A Wizard's Lizard has similar mechanics (if not as much variety in power-ups) and, for me, scratches the same itch."
