,Recommended,280040,10533532,"Posted: 19 June, 2014",all,Hyze,"Pretty cute rogue-lite game similar in style to The Binding of Issac. Plays smoothly with similar rooms extending across multiple plays, but deceptively challenging and skill-based. Some mechanics seem pretty unique, such as allowing you to continue playing as a ghost after your first 'death', which opens up some elements of the game that are only available to you as a ghost. The main playable character, Raga, is adorable. Has some mechanics similar to Rogue Legacy and other similar games that allow you to accrue larger amounts of gold across plays, with which you can purchase items. The game could use more variability in rooms, but overall it is a rewarding experience. You can pick up and play a short run for ~10-20 minutes, or play for hours at a time. If you're a fan of rogue-lite games, I highly recommend you give this one a chance."
