76561198026299729,Not Recommended,280040,20457230,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,Shhh No More Tears,"TL;DR rating:[2/5] ""An inferior Binding of Isaac clone""-Only buy if it is heavily discountedPretty much just that. This game immedieatly feels like it was trying too hard to be the binding of isaac. Now im not knocking the dev for wanting to emulate a good game, but ultimately this game doesnt add enough new stuff to the genre set it appart, and doesnt quite deliver on the basics to be satisfying.Graphics: Enemies super generic, sprites are too cartoony, almost feels like they were ordered from ""Generic-Sprites-R-Us""Sound: Equally generic and kinda... almost too upbeat. Makes it hard to take seriously.Controls: Decent, features mouse and controller support, but the controller analog sensitivity is too high, needs a activation threshhold.Gameplay: Boring... like really boring.This game feels like a student project to make a Binding of Isaac clone. It adds a FEW new things like a persistent town hub where you can buy stuff for your run. You can save townsfolk in the dungeons and each one adds persistent starting gold with which to buy items at the beginning of the run. Also you have equipment slots so you have to pick and choose what items you want, you cant just stack all the collectables you want. But other than that it is pretty much inferior in every other aspect to its source material.Im not trying to knock the dev either, I understand not every game will be a masterpiece, but it is hard to recommend spending money on something that isnt really that fun. This game got boring extremely fast and I'm a pretty patient guy. Even on the holiday sale price im a little bummed I bought it.If you REALLY just want to try it out, then get it when it goes on sale."
