,Recommended,280040,18403406,"Posted: 9 October, 2015",all,mjenso,"So far, I love that game! It's enough easy for me to painlessly start and enjoy the first level but after that the game ramps up slowly becoming more challenging and more fun! I'm not a huge fan of permadeath, I never liked Binding etc. with complex mechanics and steep learning curve but this one plays great and it knows how to motivate me to try again and again. Every time I master more skills, finish more levels, collect new objects and help more people! Still, I wish to have a ""Story mode"" where user can unlock levels and after death start on the last unlocked level. Yep, I know, it's a different game then but I would play it hard ;) BTW I found that game after listening to LostCast - best game design podcast ever! Thank you guys for your work!"
